article.headline: Florida 88, Georgia Southern 81
article.story: GAINESVILLE, Fla. -- Nick Calathes scored 21 points, Alex Tyus added 20 and Florida held off Georgia Southern 88-81 Monday, winning for the sixth time in seven games. The Gators (9-2) led 83-80 in the closing seconds before Calathes drained a 3-pointer. He scored 10 of Florida's final 19 points. Antonio Hanson led the Eagles (3-6) with 16 points and five assists. The Gators were up 58-42 early in the second half, but the Eagles used a barrage of free throws to get back in it. Consecutive 3-pointers from Colby Wohlleb and Trumaine Pearson made it 71-66 with a little more than six minutes remaining. Sandy Perry's three-point play with 38.6 seconds left cut Florida's lead to 83-80. Then Calathes hit his long-range shot to seal the win.
